---
import LegalPage from '../components/LegalPage.astro';
---

<LegalPage
  pageTitle="Cookie Policy — Parody Mechanical Solutions LLC"
  pageDesc="What cookies and storage technologies this site uses, what they do, and how you can manage or decline them."
  title="Cookie Policy"
  updated="July 19, 2026"
>
  <h2>1. What cookies are</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small files a website stores in your browser to remember
    information between visits. In this policy we use "cookies" broadly: it
    also covers similar technologies such as your browser's local storage
    (<code>localStorage</code>).
  </p>

  <h2>2. Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    This site is operated by <strong>Parody Mechanical Solutions LLC</strong>,
    a limited liability company based in Tooele, Utah, USA. For any questions
    about this policy, email us at
    <a href="mailto:kevinparody135@gmail.com">kevinparody135@gmail.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Cookies we use</h2>
  <p>
    This is primarily an informational site and uses very few cookies. These
    are the storage technologies we employ:
  </p>
  <div class="legal-table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Category</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Duration</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>pms-cookie-consent</code></td>
          <td>Local storage (first-party)</td>
          <td>Necessary</td>
          <td>
            Remembers which cookie categories you accepted or declined, so we
            don't ask again on every visit.
          </td>
          <td>Until you clear your browser data</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p>
    If we add analytics or marketing tools that set cookies in the future,
    they will only run if you consented to that category, and this table will
    be updated before they go live.
  </p>
  <p>
    The site's fonts load from Google Fonts. That request goes to Google's
    servers (which receive your IP address) but does not set cookies in your
    browser.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Categories</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Necessary:</strong> required for the site to work and to
      remember your consent choice. These can't be turned off.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Analytics:</strong> would let us measure, in aggregate, how the
      site is used so we can improve it. Only used with your permission.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Marketing:</strong> would let us show you relevant
      communications about our services on other platforms. Only used with
      your permission.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. How to manage or withdraw your choice</h2>
  <p>You can change your selection at any time from the preferences panel:</p>
  <p>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" data-cookies-open>
      Cookie settings
    </button>
  </p>
  <p>
    You can also delete or block cookies from your browser settings. Note
    that blocking necessary cookies may affect how the site works.
    Per-browser instructions:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Chrome</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/clear-cookies-and-site-data-firefox" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Mozilla Firefox</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Safari</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Microsoft Edge</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Your privacy choices (US state laws)</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell or share your personal information as those terms are
    defined under US state privacy laws (such as the California Consumer
    Privacy Act). If that ever changes, we will update this policy and
    provide the required opt-out mechanism first.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we change the cookies we use or their purpose, we will update this
    page and, when the change requires it, ask for your consent again. The
    date of the latest revision appears at the top.
  </p>

  <h2>8. More information</h2>
  <p>
    To learn how we handle the personal information you send us (for example,
    through the contact form), see our
    <a href="/privacy-policy">privacy policy</a>.
  </p>
</LegalPage>
